<h2>Notes</h2>

Dave works at the <a href="https://www.mozilla.org/">Mozilla project</a> that was created when <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Netscape">Nestscape</a>
released the source code of their browser.

He is the project leader of the <a href="http://www.bugzilla.org/">Bugzilla</a> project, which is one of the most well known
Open source Perl project. (BTW it was originally written in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tcl">Tcl</a>.)

You can follow <a href="https://twitter.com/justdavemiller">Dave Miller</a> and the <a href="https://twitter.com/justdavemiller">Bugzilla</a> project on Twitter.

<a href="http://www.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/os/">Firefox OS</a> is one of the recent project developed at te Mozilla Foundation.
The Mozilla Foundation has thousands of servers Dave helps to maintain. Most of them are used to handle the traffic of
the <a href="https://marketplace.firefox.com/">Firefox marketplace</a> and the
<a href="http://www.mozilla.org/en-US/mobile/sync/">Firefox sync</a> services.
They also have a large build-farm using to build their various product on a large number of diverse platforms.
They use <a href="http://buildbot.net/">Buildbot</a> to manage the builds.

Bugzilla uses Bazar for version control. Check out the <a href="http://www.bugzilla.org/developers/">resourced for developers</a> for more information
on how to get involved.

Both assistant project managers <a href="http://max.kanat.us/">Max Kanat-Alexander</a>,
and <a href="https://plus.google.com/103757399272253443165/">Frédéric Buclin</a> have recently moved on to other employers
and thus left the project.

In the last <a href="http://www.justdave.net/dave/2013/07/12/bugzilla-project-meeting-wednesday-july-17th-at-1400-utc/">Bugzilla developer meeting</a>,
two people: <a href="http://globau.wordpress.com/">Byron Jones</a> (globau on IRC) and <a href="">Simon Green</a> have steped up for the patch approval process which is necessary
to accept patches from every developer. You can watch the entire meeting on <a href="http://youtu.be/vxVGhaPFaZc">YouTube</a>.

<a href="irc://irc.mozilla.org/bugzilla">#bugzilla on irc.mozilla.org</a>, you can access it via
<a href="http://landfill.bugzilla.org/irc/"> Bugzilla IRC Gateway</a> without installing anything.

